Class EquivalentTransitionsMatcher

    public class EquivalentTransitionsMatcher
extends org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.api.impl.BaseMatcher<EquivalentTransitionsMatch>
    Generated pattern matcher API of the org.eclipse.viatra.cep.core.engine.compiler.equivalentTransitions pattern, providing pattern-specific query methods.

    Use the pattern matcher on a given model via on(ViatraQueryEngine), e.g. in conjunction with ViatraQueryEngine#on(Notifier).

    Matches of the pattern will be represented as EquivalentTransitionsMatch.

    Original source: 

     pattern
 equivalentTransitions(transition1 : TypedTransition, transition2 : TypedTransition, preState : State, postState : State) {
        transition1 != transition2;
        
        find sameBooleanTransitionType(transition1, transition2);
        
        Transition.preState(transition1, preState);
        Transition.preState(transition2, preState);
 
        Transition.postState(transition1, postState);
        Transition.postState(transition2, postState);
 
        TypedTransition.guards(transition1, guard1);
        TypedTransition.guards(transition2, guard2);
 
        Guard.eventType(guard1, et1);
        Guard.eventType(guard2, et2);
 
        et1 == et2;
 
        Automaton.states(automaton, preState);
        Automaton.states(automaton, postState);
 }
    See Also:
    EquivalentTransitionsMatch, EquivalentTransitionsProcessor, EquivalentTransitionsQuerySpecification
